classes.name: DriverManager
classes.description: The basic service for managing a set of JDBC drivers. Provides static methods for obtaining database connections.

methods.name: getConnection

params.description: A database URL of the form jdbc:subprotocol:subname

returns.description: A connection to the URL

methods.description: Attempts to establish a connection to the given database URL.

params.name: password
params.description: The user's password

returns.description: A connection to the URL

methods.description: Attempts to establish a connection to the given database URL with the given username and password.

methods.name: getConnection

params.name: url
params.description: A database URL of the form jdbc:subprotocol:subname

classes.name: Connection
classes.description: A connection (session) with a specific database. SQL statements are executed and results are returned within the context of a connection.

methods.name: prepareStatement

params.name: sql
params.description: An SQL statement that may contain one or more '?' parameter placeholders

returns.description: A new PreparedStatement object containing the pre-compiled SQL statement

methods.description: Creates a PreparedStatement object for sending parameterized SQL statements to the database.

methods.name: createStatement

returns.description: A new Statement object

methods.description: Creates a Statement object for sending SQL statements to the database.

methods.name: prepareCall

params.description: An SQL statement that may contain one or more '?' parameter placeholders, typically a JDBC call escape syntax

methods.description: Creates a CallableStatement object for calling database stored procedures.

methods.name: close
methods.description: Releases this Connection object's database and JDBC resources immediately instead of waiting for them to be automatically released.

methods.name: isClosed

returns.description: True if this Connection object is closed; false if it is still open

methods.description: Retrieves whether this Connection object has been closed.

methods.name: commit
methods.description: Makes all changes made since the previous commit/rollback permanent and releases any database locks currently held by this Connection object.

methods.name: rollback
methods.description: Undoes all changes made in the current transaction and releases any database locks currently held by this Connection object.

methods.name: setAutoCommit

params.name: autoCommit
params.description: True to enable auto-commit mode; false to disable it

methods.description: Sets this connection's auto-commit mode to the given state.

methods.description: Retrieves the current auto-commit mode for this Connection object.

methods.name: getMetaData

methods.description: Retrieves a DatabaseMetaData object that contains metadata about the database to which this Connection object represents a connection.

methods.name: setCatalog

params.name: catalog
params.description: The name of a catalog (subspace in this Connection object's database) in which to work

methods.description: Sets the given catalog name in order to select a subspace of this Connection object's database in which to work.

methods.name: getCatalog

returns.description: The current catalog name or null if there is none

methods.description: Retrieves this Connection object's current catalog name.

methods.name: setSchema

params.name: schema

methods.name: getSchema

returns.description: The current schema name or null if there is none

methods.description: Retrieves this Connection object's current schema name.

methods.name: setReadOnly

params.name: readOnly
params.description: True enables read-only mode; false disables it

methods.name: isReadOnly

returns.description: True if this Connection object is read-only; false otherwise

methods.description: Retrieves whether this Connection object is in read-only mode.

methods.name: setTransactionIsolation

methods.description: Attempts to change the transaction isolation level for this Connection object to the one given.

methods.name: getTransactionIsolation

returns.description: The current transaction isolation level

methods.description: Retrieves this Connection object's current transaction isolation level.

methods.name: isValid

params.name: timeout
params.description: The time in seconds to wait for the database operation to complete

returns.description: True if the connection is valid; false otherwise

methods.description: Returns true if the connection has not been closed and is still valid. The driver submits a query on the connection or uses some other mechanism to verify the connection is still valid.

fields.name: TRANSACTION_NONE
fields.description: Indicates that transactions are not supported.

fields.name: TRANSACTION_READ_UNCOMMITTED
fields.description: Indicates that dirty reads, non-repeatable reads, and phantom reads can occur.

fields.name: TRANSACTION_READ_COMMITTED
fields.description: Indicates that dirty reads are prevented; non-repeatable reads and phantom reads can occur.

fields.name: TRANSACTION_REPEATABLE_READ
fields.description: Indicates that dirty reads and non-repeatable reads are prevented; phantom reads can occur.

fields.name: TRANSACTION_SERIALIZABLE
fields.description: Indicates that dirty reads, non-repeatable reads, and phantom reads are prevented.
